The paper discusses a technique for training deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the issue of covariate shift, which is a problem in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the same model for training and inference, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
